{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}

{% block content %}
<main class="main-container">
      {% include "partials/hero.njk" %}

      <div class="page-layout">
        {%- include "partials/aside.njk" %}

        <section class="article">
          <figure class="figure">
            <img
              class="figure__img"
              src="src/images/static/dragon-main.webp"
              alt="Human and two-headed basilisk"
              width="1024"
              height="557"
            />
            <figcaption class="figure__caption">Photo caption</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <h2 class="section-title section-title--left">The Basilisks NFT</h2>
          <a class="button button--primary" href="#">Gaming</a>
          <div class="info">
            <!--Independent element-->
            <span class="info__profile">
              <img
                class="info__profile-icon"
                src="#"
                alt="user-icon"
                width="16"
                height="16"
              />
              Tony Nguyen
            </span>
            <time class="info__date" datetime="2022-06-20">
              <img
                class="info__calendar-icon"
                src="#"
                alt="calendar"
                width="16"
                height="16"
              />
              20 Jun 2022
            </time>
          </div>
          <p class="article__text">
            The Basilisks that<span class="article__spotlight"> players</span>
            collect are represented with NFTs on Ethereum's blockchain with
            real-world value. Players use the
            <a class="article__highlight" href="#">Basilisks they have</a>
            gathered to battle other players to win ether (ETH).
          </p>
          <p class="article__text">
            In Balthazar Dragons, players are immersed in a 3D open world to
            explore and capture dragon-like beasts called Basilisks. Balthazar
            Dragons is an upcoming fantasy role-playing game developed on the
            Ethereum blockchain by a decentralized autonomous organization (DAO)
            called the Balthazar DAO.
          </p>
          <ul class="article__list">
            <li class="article__item">
              The Basilisks that players collect are represented with NFTs on
              Ethereum's blockchain with real-world value. Players use the
              Basilisks they have gathered to battle other players to win ether
              (ETH).
            </li>
            <li class="article__item">
              In Balthazar Dragons, players are immersed in a 3D open world to
              explore and capture dragon-like beasts called Basilisks. Balthazar
              Dragons is an upcoming fantasy role-playing
              <a class="article__highlight" href="#">game developed</a> on the
              Ethereum blockchain by a decentralized autonomous organization
              (DAO) called the Balthazar DAO.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <ul class="article__custom-list">
            <!--Binabox logos will be added as a marker with CSS-->
            <li class="article__custom-item">List name 1</li>
            <li class="article__custom-item">List name 2</li>
            <li class="article__custom-item">List name 3</li>
            <li class="article__custom-item">List name 4</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="quote-wrapper">
            <blockquote class="quote">
              <p class="quote__text">
                “The first huge metaverse arena to arrange live sports, hang out
                and even make bets and wagers”
              </p>
            </blockquote>
            <div class="quote__footer">
              <img
                class="quote__rating-icon"
                src="#"
                alt="Rating icon"
                width="15"
                height="15"
              />
              <span class="quote__rating">8.5/10</span>
              <cite class="quote__author">Markout Corporation</cite>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="figure-wrapper">
            <figure class="figure">
              <img
                class="figure__img"
                src="src/images/static/dragon-head.webp"
                alt="Dragon head"
                width="500"
                height="394"
              />
              <figcaption class="figure__caption">Photo caption</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="figure">
              <img
                class="figure__img"
                src="src/images/static/dragon-and-human.webp"
                alt="Dragon and human"
                width="500"
                height="394"
              />
              <figcaption class="figure__caption">Photo caption</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
          <h3 class="article__subtitle">
            NFTs are digital assets that represent real-world objects
          </h3>
          <!--Article__subtitle 28px left-->
          <p class="article__text">
            Setting up your avatar and personalizing your nickname on Binance is
            quick and easy. Users can go to binance.com under Dashboard >
            Settings > My Profile > Avatar and Nickname. For those of you who
            own NFT assets, you can select the NFT you want to use from your
            collection as your avatar to personalize your profile. For users who
            do not own any NFT avatars, check out the NFT avatar collections
            page to get started.
          </p>
          <p class="article__text">
            Alternatively, if you're on nft.binance.com, go to User Center >
            Settings > Basic > Set Avatar and Nickname, and you'll be redirected
            to the main site. Binance NFT Creators have the option of setting
            their Avatars on nft.binance.com. Once you set your new unique
            nickname, it will be standardized and used across the Binance
            ecosystem.
          </p>
          <h3 class="article__subtitle">NFT Avatar Generators</h3>
          <!--Article__subtitle 28px left-->
          <p class="article__text">
            You can find a range of NFT marketplaces where you can buy existing
            NFTs or list your own NFTs for sale.
          </p>
          <footer class="article__footer">
            <ul class="action-tag">
              <li class="action-tag__item">
                <span class="article__footer-label">Tags:</span>
              </li>
              <li class="action-tag__item">
                <a class="action-tag__link" href="#">NFT</a>
              </li>
              <li class="action-tag__item">
                <a class="action-tag__link" href="#">ICO</a>
              </li>
              <li class="action-tag__item">
                <a class="action-tag__link" href="#">Crypto</a>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="action-tag">
              <li class="action-tag__item">
                <span class="article__footer-label">Share:</span>
              </li>
              <li class="action-tag__item">
                <a class="action-tag__link" href="#">
                  <img
                    class="action-tag__img"
                    src="#"
                    alt="Twitter logo"
                    width="16"
                    height="16"
                  />
                </a>
              </li>
              <li class="action-tag__item">
                <a class="action-tag__link" href="#">
                  <img
                    class="action-tag__img"
                    src="#"
                    alt="Facebook logo"
                    width="16"
                    height="16"
                  />
                </a>
              </li>
              <li class="action-tag__item">
                <a class="action-tag__link" href="#">
                  <img
                    class="action-tag__img"
                    src="#"
                    alt="Instagram logo"
                    width="16"
                    height="16"
                  />
                </a>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </footer>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
{% endblock %}
